e+richmond+palladium+and+sun-telegram+%28richmond,+ind.%29+1907-1939&fo=json"}, {"count": 3203926, "title": "chronicling america", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/collections/chronicling-america/?fo=json"}, {"count": 3225157, "title": "serial and government publications division", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=partof:serial+and+government+publications+division&fo=json"}], "partof_collection": ["chronicling america"], "partof_division": ["serial and government publications division"], "partof_title": ["the richmond palladium and sun-telegram (richmond, ind.) 1907-1939"], "place_of_publication": "Richmond, Ind.", "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "raw_lccn": "sn 86058226 ", "reel_numbers": ["00271745369"], "resources": [{"files": 14, "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:in:batch_in_everettcase_ver01:data:sn86058226:00271745369:1921022401:0151/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86058226/1921-02-24/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "rights": ["<p>The Library of Congress believes that the newspapers in Chronicling America are in the public domain or have no known copyright restrictions.  Newspapers published in the United States more than 95 years ago are in the public domain in their entirety. Any newspapers in Chronicling America that were published less than 95 years ago are also believed to be in the public domain, but may contain some copyrighted third party materials. Researchers using newspapers published less than 95 years ago should be alert for modern content (for example, registered and renewed for copyright and published with notice) that may be copyrighted.  Responsibility for making an independent legal assessment of an item and securing any necessary permissions ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 14.332207, "shard": "07", "shelf_id": "sn86058226, 1921-02-24, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/in", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["newspapers", "wayne county (ind.)", "wayne", "richmond (ind.)", "richmond", "wayne county", "indiana", "united states"], "subject_headings": ["Richmond (Ind.)--Newspapers", "Wayne County (Ind.)--Newspapers", "Indiana--Richmond", "Indiana--Wayne County", "United States--Indiana--Wayne--Richmond"], "subjects": [{"indiana": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:indiana&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"richmond": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:richmond&fo=json"}, {"richmond (ind.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:richmond+%28ind.%29&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}, {"wayne": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:wayne&fo=json"}, {"wayne county": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:wayne+county&fo=json"}, {"wayne county (ind.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:wayne+county+%28ind.%29&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2023-08-22T23:37:43.654Z", "title": "The Richmond palladium and sun-telegram (Richmond, Ind.), February 24, 1921", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn86058226/1921-02-24/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn86058226/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn86058226", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/67830181-bdcf-5446-b95a-49dc821f756d"], "batch": ["in_everettcase_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1907", "description": ["Daily Vol. 31, no. 363 (Mar. 17, 1907)-v. 109, no. 6 (Jan. 7, 1939). Publisher's name from Miller, John W. Indiana newspaper bibliog. Issue called: 100th Anniversary ed., Jan. 1, 1931. Progressive party paper; opposed the Ku Klux Klan and the Republican party. Cf. Miller. Issues for Mar. 17-29, 1907 were numbered: v. 31, no. 363--as were all issues of the preceding title dating back to Feb. 16, 1907. Mar. 30, 1907 issue is numbered, v. 32, no. 78. There was a special supplement published on Jan. 1, 1931 which celebrated the 100th anniversary of the paper. Archived issues are available in digital format from the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. Formed by the merger of: Farm palladium, Richmond palladium (Richmond, Ind. : 1906 : Daily) and Richmond sun-telegram (Richmond, Ind. : 1906 : Daily). Published until about 1917 also in a weekly edition called: Richmond sun. Telegram. Richmond item (Richmond, Ind.) (DLC)sn 86058237 (OCoLC)13089930 Palladium-item and sun-telegram (DLC)sn 86058238 (OCoLC)13089951"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:05.831Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-06", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-06"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn86058226/", "image_url": [], "index": 1, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [39.827286, -84.890357], "location": ["wayne", "richmond", "wayne county", "indiana", "united states"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-84.890357, 39.827286], "number": ["online resource", "13085166", "1", "microfilm service copy", "sn86058224", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn86058226/1922-12-30/ed-1/", "new york state libr", "sn86058238", "sn86058226", "sn86058237", "indiana state libr", "2023-08-09t14:42:45.433113", "2572-8911", "filson hist soc, the", "2025-11-07t12:27:45.400000", "original", "duke univ libr", "sn86058225", "sn82015675", "detroit public library", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn86058226/1907-03-17/ed-1/", "5167", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["the richmond palladium and sun-telegram (richmond, ind.) 1907-1939", "catalog", "chronicling america", "serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 71.90809, "shelf_id": "Newspaper AN", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["newspapers", "wayne county (ind.)", "wayne", "richmond (ind.)", "richmond", "wayne county", "indiana", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T09:18:25.078Z", "title": "The Richmond palladium and sun-telegram", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn86058226/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218544/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1855", "dates": ["[1855 TO 1875]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with vol. XVII [XXVI], no. 1 (December 20, 1855); ceased in the fall of 1975. Description based on: Vol. XVII [XXVI], no. 1 (December 20, 1855); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed February 14, 2018). Latest issue consulted: Vol. XLV, no. 33, whole number, 2321 (Oct. 27, 1875) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed February 14, 2018). Richmond weekly palladium 2576-8956 (DLC) 2018218546 (OCoLC)1023028451"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:41.529Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218544/", "image_url": [], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "location": ["wayne", "richmond", "wayne county", "indiana", "united states"], "number": ["1023023897", "online resource", "2576-8913", "2018218544", "2018218546", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "the richmond palladium (richmond, wayne county, ind.) 1855-1875 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 62.733402, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "wayne county (ind.)", "wayne", "richmond (ind.)", "richmond", "wayne county", "indiana", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:55:54.213Z", "title": "The Richmond palladium", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2018218544/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218546/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1875", "dates": ["[1875 TO 1905]"], "description": ["Weekly Began in the fall of 1875; ceased in late 1905. Published in a daily ed. called Jan. 1876-Jan. 1904: Richmond daily palladium (Richmond, Ind. : 1876); Jan. 1904-June 1905, Daily palladium (Richmond, Ind.); June 1905-Mar. 1906; Richmond daily palladium (Richmond, Ind. : 1905). Description based on: Vol. 45, no. 39, whole no. 2327 (December 9, 1875); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed February 14, 2018). Latest issue consulted: Vol. 45, no. 39, whole no. 2327 (December 9, 1875) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed February 14, 2018). Farm palladium"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:41.529Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218546/", "image_url": [], "index": 3, "language": ["english"], "location": ["wayne", "richmond", "wayne county", "indiana", "united states"], "number": ["2017218617", "1023028451", "online resource", "2018218544", "2018218546", "2017218857", "2017218858", "2576-8956", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["richmond weekly palladium (richmond, wayne county, ind.) 1875-1905 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 62.733402, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "wayne county (ind.)", "wayne", "richmond (ind.)", "richmond", "wayne county", "indiana", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:55:54.213Z", "title": "Richmond weekly palladium", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2018218546/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218577/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1854", "dates": ["[1854 TO 1855]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with volume XXV, number 1 (December 22, 1854); ceased with volume XXV, number 52 (December 13, 1855). Publisher: D. P. Holloway, B. W. Davis & I. S. Drake, March 23-December 13, 1855. Description based on: Volume XXV, number 3 (January 5, 1855); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed February 14, 2018). Latest issue consulted: Volume XXV, number 52 (December 13, 1855) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed February 14, 2018). Richmond palladium (Richmond, Ind. : 1855) 2576-8913 (DLC) 2018218544 (OCoLC)023023897"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:41.529Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218577/", "image_url": [], "index": 4, "language": ["english"], "location": ["wayne", "richmond", "wayne county", "indiana", "united states"], "number": ["online resource", "2017218618", "2018218544", "1023019830", "2018218577", "2576-8891", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "the richmond indiana palladium (richmond, wayne county, (ind.)) 1854-1855 [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 62.733402, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "wayne county (ind.)", "wayne", "richmond (ind.)", "wayne county", "richmond", "indiana", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:55:54.213Z", "title": "The Richmond Indiana palladium", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2018218577/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2017218614/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1831", "dates": ["[1831 TO 1837]"], "description": ["Weekly Began in January 1831; ceased with volume VII, number 23 (June 14th, 1837). Publisher: D. P. Holloway and R. W. Davis, <January 7>-June 14, 1837. Issues for <Feb. 9, 1833-Mar. 22, 1834> called also <whole no. 109-whole no. 167>. Description based on: Volume I, number 2 (January 8, 1831); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 12, 2017). Latest issue consulted: Volume VII, number 23 (June 14th, 1837) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 12, 2017). Richmond Indiana palladium (Richmond, Ind. : 1837)"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:38.331Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017218614/", "image_url": [], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "location": ["wayne", "richmond", "wayne county", "indiana", "united states"], "number": ["2572-6994", "online resource", "982193646", "2017218614", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "richmond palladium (richmond, wayne county, indiana) 1831-1837 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 62.733402, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "wayne county (ind.)", "wayne", "richmond (ind.)", "richmond", "wayne county", "indiana", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:54:30.872Z", "title": "Richmond palladium", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2017218614/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2017218616/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1907", "dates": ["[1907 TO 1939]"], "description": ["Daily Began with vol. XXI, no. 363 (March 17, 1907); ceased with January 7, 1939 issue. Publisher's name from Miller, John W. Indiana newspaper bibliog. Issue called: 100th Anniversary ed., Jan. 1, 1931. Progressive party paper; opposed the Ku Klux Klan and the Republican party. Cf. Miller. Issues for Mar. 17-29, 1907 were numbered: v. 31, no. 363--as were all issues of the preceding title dating back to Feb. 16, 1907. Mar. 30, 1907 issue is numbered, v. 32, no. 78. There was a special supplement published on Jan. 1, 1931 which celebrated the 100th anniversary of the paper. Formed by the merger of: Farm palladium, Richmond palladium (Richmond, Ind. : 1906 : Daily) and Richmond sun-telegram (Richmond, Ind. : 1906 : Daily). Published until about 1917 also in a weekly edition called: Richmond sun. Telegram. Description based on: Vol. XXI, no. 363 (March 17, 1907); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 26, 2017). Latest issue consulted: Vol. XCII, no. 94 (April 20, 1922) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 26, 2017). Vol. 45, no. 43 (January 1, 1920); title from PDF masthead (Reveal Digital website, viewed November 12, 1925) Vol. 93, no. 36 (February 10, 1923) (viewed November 12, 1925) Richmond item (Richmond, Ind.) Palladium-item and sun-telegram"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:38.331Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017218616/", "image_url": [], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["wayne", "richmond", "wayne county", "indiana", "united states"], "number": ["2017218859", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "online resource", "984345583", "2017218616", "2572-892x"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["the richmond palladium and sun-telegram (richmond, indiana) 1907-1939 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial an